findings.title: Potential unauthorized script upgrade
findings.description: The smart contract may allow an unauthorized user to upgrade the script, potentially leading to security vulnerabilities.

findings.title: Minting of unlimited number of sundae tokens
findings.description: The contract allows minting an unlimited number of tokens without any restriction.

findings.title: Unprotected functions
findings.description: Multiple unprotected functions found in the smart contract, including transfer, approve, transferFrom, increaseAllowance, decreaseAllowance, deliver, excludeFromReward, includeInReward, excludeFromFee, setBlackList, enableTrading, includeInFee, setBuyFee, setSellFee, setNumTokensSellToAddToLiquidity, updateRouter, setMaxWallet, and setMaxBuyAmount
